sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant OP as Operator<br/>(Asset Console)
    participant EE as Execution Engine
    participant KG as Key Guardian
    participant HSM as HSM / KMS
    participant TS as Transaction Signer
    participant BC as Blockchain

    Note over OP,BC: Key Generation + Provisioning

    OP->>EE: Request key provisioning
    EE->>KG: Generate key pair
    KG->>HSM: Create key in secure enclave
    HSM-->>KG: Key reference (private key never leaves HSM)
    KG->>KG: Store key metadata + access policy
    KG-->>EE: Public key + key ID
    EE-->>OP: Key provisioned (address assigned)

    Note over OP,BC: Key Guardian holds metadata. HSM holds private key. No single component has both.

    Note over OP,BC: Transaction Signing Request

    OP->>EE: Submit transaction
    EE->>KG: Request signing authorization
    KG->>KG: Validate requester role (RBAC)
    KG->>KG: Check signing policy (limits, whitelist)

    alt Policy requires multi-approval
        KG->>OP: Request second approver
        OP->>KG: Second approval received
    end

    KG->>TS: Issue signing token (time-bound)

    Note over KG,TS: Signing token is scoped: specific key, specific transaction, limited TTL.

    TS->>HSM: Sign payload with key reference
    HSM->>HSM: Validate signing policy
    HSM-->>TS: Signed transaction

    Note over TS,BC: Transaction Signer cannot choose which key to use. Key Guardian dictates.

    TS->>BC: Broadcast signed transaction
    BC-->>TS: Transaction receipt + block confirmation
    TS-->>EE: Execution confirmed
    EE-->>OP: Transaction success

    Note over OP,BC: Key Rotation (Periodic)

    OP->>EE: Initiate key rotation
    EE->>KG: Rotate key
    KG->>HSM: Generate new key pair
    HSM-->>KG: New key reference
    KG->>KG: Deprecate old key, update access policy
    KG-->>EE: Rotation complete
    EE-->>OP: New key active, old key archived

    Note over KG: [CLIENT: Configure HSM provider, signing policies, and rotation schedule here]
